# Production Environment Variables Configuration

# IMPORTANT: For production deployment, ensure all these variables are set correctly

# Database Configuration
# NOTE: Special characters in password MUST be URL-encoded!
# Example: & becomes %26, @ becomes %40, # becomes %23
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:[URL_ENCODED_PASSWORD]@db.[PROJECT_REF].supabase.co:5432/postgres

# Supabase Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://[PROJECT_REF].supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Google Places API (for cafe features)
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_PLACES_KEY=your_google_places_api_key_here

# Production Checklist:
# 1. Replace [PROJECT_REF] with your Supabase project reference
# 2. Replace [URL_ENCODED_PASSWORD] with your URL-encoded database password
# 3. Add these to your deployment platform (Vercel, Netlify, etc.)
# 4. In Supabase Dashboard:
#    - Add production URL to Authentication > URL Configuration > Redirect URLs
#    - Update Site URL to production domain
# 5. Ensure Supabase project is active (not paused)